Subject: [PATCH] feat(shadow): full Shadow trait + hasTrait canonical
 migration
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Shadow trait (per owner's full description):
- data/traits/traits.json: added 'shadow' trait with:
  * attributeBonus: { STR: 2, END: 2 }
  * attributeLimits: { STR/END: 6..12, CHA/INT: max 8 }
  * skillMaxValue: 4 (hard cap on all skills)
  * immunities: radiation, poison
  * effects: ['stealth_boy_addiction'] (placeholder; see effects.js)
- i18n/{ru-RU,en-EN}/data/system/traits.json: full Shadow description.
- data/origins/origins.json: shadow.traitIds = ['shadow'].

hasTrait migration to canonical id (PATCH 1/2 + 2/2 merged):
- All 14 trait modals: onSelect(name, mods) -> onSelect(traitId, name, mods).
- SurvivorModal (multi-trait): onSelect(selectedIds[], name, mods).
- CharacterScreen.handleSelectTrait already accepts ids on main.
- CharacterContext.hasTrait: canonical-only, NO legacy fallback to
  trait.name / selectedTraitNames (per project rule: no aliases at runtime).
- WeaponsAndArmorScreen.js:
  hasTrait('Техника спуска') -> hasTrait('ncr-technique-of-descent')
  hasTrait('Пехотинец')      -> hasTrait('ncr-infantryman')

trait.name stays as-is (localized display only).
trait.id is canonical (logic only). Two separate roles, not aliased.
